{{WORKFLOW_EXAMPLES}}

Authoring deliverables for any touched or new workflow:
- clear objective
- obvious core flow
- explicit role/step topology
- explicit control flow
- explicit route grammar
- explicit artifact contract
- narrow runtime-injected control contract
- concise prompt templates
- explicit verification/evidence contract
- explicit rework/replan/block/fail policy
- shared validation helpers where appropriate

Outcome standard:
- The bootstrap must make future recursive cycles more likely to converge toward a smaller, clearer, more reusable architecture.
- Prefer work that improves authoring leverage across multiple workflows.
